            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google's Helpful Content Update is a series of algorithm rollouts from August 2022 to March 2024 that introduced a site-wide ranking signal penalising content made primarily for search engines rather than for people. The signal generated domain-level scores, meaning thin pages on one part of a site could suppress well-written pages on another part.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does the Helpful Content Update target AI content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The update targets content lacking genuine value for readers, regardless of production method. Mass-produced AI content with no human editing, original research, or expert perspective is a primary target. AI-assisted content with strong human editorial oversight and original insight is not targeted.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I know if the Helpful Content Update affected my site?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Monitor Google Search Console for gradual, sustained organic traffic declines starting around documented rollout dates: August 2022, December 2022, September 2023, and March 2024. Unlike a manual penalty, there is no notification. The signal tends to cause slow, compounding declines rather than overnight drops.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I recover from a Helpful Content Update hit?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, but recovery is measured in months, not weeks. Audit your site systematically: identify thin pages, remove or consolidate the weakest content, improve surviving pages with original research and genuine expertise. The system re-evaluates continuously. Sites that have recovered typically show 6-12 months of sustained improvement before significant ranking gains return.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is the Helpful Content Update still active in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>In March 2024, Google folded the Helpful Content System into its core ranking systems rather than running it as a separate algorithm. The signal still influences rankings, but it now operates as part of Google's main quality evaluation framework rather than as a distinct named system.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

